inematic representations engage in the ongoing dialogue between nature and culture, Monica Seger contributes to the transnational expansion of environmental humanities. Her book also introduces an ecocritical framework to Italian studies in English. Rejecting a stark dichotomy between human construction and unspoilt nature, Landscapes in Between will be of interest to all those studying the fraught relationship between humanity and environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aEcology in literature. 0aEcology in motion picturesxItaly. 0aEcology in motion pictures. 0aItalian literaturexHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aItalian literaturexHistory and criticismx21st century. 0aItalian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aItalian literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLandscapes in literature. 0aLandscapes in motion pictures. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxItaly. 0aMotion pictureszItalyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311049093008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066769108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015z978311060681208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019z978311065878140uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261964740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442619647423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442619647.jpg  a978-3-11-049093-0  UTP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-060